A factorial is shown by an exclamation point(!) following a number. The factorial of 5, or 5!, is calculated by (5)(4)(3)(2)(1) = 120.

Assuming `n` is an integer greater than 1, choose the method that will return `n!`.

```java
public static int f(int n) {
    int factorial = 1;
    for (int i = n; i > 0 ; i-- ) {
        factorial *= n;
    }
    return factorial;
}
```

```java
public static int f(int n) {
    int factorial = 1;
    int j = 1;
    while (j <= n) {
        factorial *= j;
        j++;
    }
    return factorial;
}
```

```java
public static int f(int n) {
    if (n == 1)
        return n;
    return n * f(n - 1);
}
```

